CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 3, 1958, pg. 4A reads: "Talented Teens - SHown harmonizing for the audience at Schenley High School last Saturday on the All-City Student Council show were these six young people. From left to right are John Brown, Bernard Carpenter, Ronald Johnson, Geneva Brown, Robert Morrison and Byron Moore.  The young men make up the singing  group known as the Savoys, and Miss Brown is a student at Peabody High School. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of singing group The Savoys, from left: John Brown, Bernard Carpenter, Ronald Johnson, Robert Morrison, and Byron Moore, posed with Geneva Brown in Schenley High School for the All-City Student Council show
